title: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expect class
description: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? The output is 'MySomeClass'.
OB: When calling the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method with a Set of classes containing the class 'MySomeClass', the output is 'MySomeClass'.
EB: The expected behavior is that when calling the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method with a Set of classes, the output should not be 'MySomeClass.' The classSet should not be treated as an expect class for this method.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, perform the following steps:
1. Call the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method with a Set of classes that includes 'MySomeClass'.
2. Observe that the output is 'MySomeClass,' which is not the expected behavior.
